Java (JDK) Versions & Key Features
  ✅ JDK 1.0 (1996)
      Initial release
      Basic OOP, JVM, AWT
  
  ✅ JDK 1.2 – “Collections Framework” (1998)
      Introduced Collections API
      ArrayList, HashMap, HashSet
  
  ✅ JDK 1.3
      JVM improvements
      No major language changes
  
  ✅ JDK 1.4 (2002)
      assert keyword
      Exception chaining
      NIO (Non-blocking IO)
  
  🚀 JDK 5 (1.5) – BIG RELEASE 👉 Most important version
       Generics (List<String>)
      Annotations
      Autoboxing/Unboxing
      Enhanced for-loop
      Enum
      Varargs
  
  🚀 JDK 6
      Performance improvements
      JDBC enhancements
  
  🚀 JDK 7
      Try-with-resources
      Diamond operator <>
      Multi-catch
      NIO.2 (Files API)
  
  🔥 JDK 8 (MOST IMPORTANT) 👉 Used everywhere
      Lambda expressions
      Streams API
      Functional interfaces
      Default & static methods in interfaces
      Optional class
      Date & Time API (java.time
                      
  🚀 JDK 9
      Module system (Project Jigsaw)
      JShell (REPL)
      Private methods in interfaces 
      Deprecated/Removed: Java EE modules deprecated
  
  🚀 JDK 10
      var (local variable type inference)
  
  🚀 JDK 11 (LTS) 👉 Very important production version
      New HTTP Client API
      String methods (isBlank, lines)
      Lambda improvements
      Removed: Java EE & CORBA modules ❌
  
  🚀 JDK 12–13
      Switch expression (preview)
                     
  🚀 JDK 14
      Switch expressions (stable)
      Records (preview)
      Helpful NullPointerExceptions
  
  🚀 JDK 15
      Text blocks (""")
      Sealed classes (preview)
  
  🚀 JDK 16
      Records (stable)
  
  🚀 JDK 17 (LTS) 👉 Current enterprise standard (very important)
      Sealed classes (stable)
      Pattern matching (instanceof)
      Strong encapsulation      
      Removed:  Security manager deprecated
  
  🚀 JDK 18–20
      Performance improvements
      Virtual threads (preview starts)
  
  🔥 JDK 21 (LTS – VERY IMPORTANT NOW) 👉 Latest major LTS 
      Virtual Threads (Project Loom) ✅
      Pattern Matching for switch
      Record patterns
      Sequenced collections
  
  🚀 JDK 22+ (Latest ongoing)
      Continuous improvements
      Foreign Function & Memory API (preview → stable soon)
